abstract = {Large Language Models (LLMs) may one day replace search engines as the primary portal to information on the Web. In this opinion paper, we investigate the societal challenges that such a change could bring. We focus on the roles of LLM Providers, Content Creators, and End Users, and identify 15 types of challenges. With each, we show current mitigation strategies – both from the technical perspective and the legal perspective. We also discuss the impact of each challenge and point out future research opportunities.},
